HEADWORD: Laurin
<hw>Lau"rin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>laurine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white crystalline
substance extracted from the fruit of the bay (<spn>Laurus
nobilis</spn>), and consisting of a complex mixture of glycerin ethers
of several organic acids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Laurinol</ent>⟦br⟧
